cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "SciMD — Scientific Markdown for the AI Era"
message: "If you use SciMD in your research or software, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Avilés Calderón"
    given-names: "Juan Francisco"
    email: "avilesfran21@gmail.com"
repository-code: "https://github.com/avifranca/scimd"
url: "https://github.com/avifranca/scimd"
abstract: >
  SciMD is an open-source plain-text document format and reference implementation
  designed for scientific and technical writing in the AI era. It enables
  AI-readable scientific papers with structured charts, diagrams, equations,
  and semantic sections optimized for RAG pipelines and LLM training.
keywords:
  - scientific-writing
  - document-format
  - markdown
  - ai
  - rag
  - llm
  - plain-text
license: MIT
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-03-17"
